Web Demo Using IMDb Data

A demo web application showing various features such as:

 - Javalin web framework
 - Embedded Jetty web server
 - Thymeleaf templating engine
 - Jdbi relational data access
 - Hikari database connection pooling
 - Hibernate Validator data validation
 - Gson JSON serialization/deserialization
 - jQuery UI user interface widgets
 - Datatables tabular data display
 - Skeleton responsive UI/layout boilerplate

It is not intended to be a fully functioning web application. It implements basic select and update functionality, but has no create or delete capabilities. The site uses publicly available data from IMDb to demonstrate its features.

Packages 
Package Description
org.northcoder.titlewebdemo
Javalin web server set-up and routes.
org.northcoder.titlewebdemo.beans
Java beans representing core entities such as Title and Talent, plus supporting entities such as TalentInTitle which represents a resolution entity between Title and Talent.
org.northcoder.titlewebdemo.controller
Classes responsible for assembling data used by the MVC model objects.
org.northcoder.titlewebdemo.dao
Data Access Object classes, which control access to the underlying database.
org.northcoder.titlewebdemo.util
Various utility classes, including configuration of the embedded Jetty server.
org.northcoder.titlewebdemo.validation
Custom Hibernate validation logic and annotations.
